argumentText:
ARGUMENT
x

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | #P_vex | |- x e. _V |
| 2 |  | #P_id | |- ( A C_ B -> A C_ B ) |
| 3 |  | #P_id | |- ( x e. ~P A -> x e. ~P A ) |
| 4 |  | #P_elpwi | |- ( x e. ~P A -> x C_ A ) |
| 5 | 3, 4 | #P_syl | |- ( x e. ~P A -> x C_ A ) |
| 6 |  | #P_sstr2 | |- ( x C_ A -> ( A C_ B -> x C_ B ) ) |
| 7 | 6 | #P_impcom | |- ( ( A C_ B /\ x C_ A ) -> x C_ B ) |
| 8 | 2, 5, 7 | #P_syl2an | |- ( ( A C_ B /\ x e. ~P A ) -> x C_ B ) |
| 9 |  | #P_elpwg | |- ( x e. _V -> ( x e. ~P B <-> x C_ B ) ) |
| 10 | 9 | #P_biimpar | |- ( ( x e. _V /\ x C_ B ) -> x e. ~P B ) |
| 11 | 1, 8, 10 | #P_eel021old | |- ( ( A C_ B /\ x e. ~P A ) -> x e. ~P B ) |
| 12 | 11 | #P_ex | |- ( A C_ B -> ( x e. ~P A -> x e. ~P B ) ) |
| 13 | 12 | #P_alrimiv | |- ( A C_ B -> A. x ( x e. ~P A -> x e. ~P B ) ) |
| 14 |  | #P_dfss2 | |- ( ~P A C_ ~P B <-> A. x ( x e. ~P A -> x e. ~P B ) ) |
| 15 | 14 | #P_biimpri | |- ( A. x ( x e. ~P A -> x e. ~P B ) -> ~P A C_ ~P B ) |
| 16 | 13, 15 | #P_syl | |- ( A C_ B -> ~P A C_ ~P B ) |
| 17 | 16 | #P_iin1 | |- ( A C_ B -> ~P A C_ ~P B ) |
\
 If a class is a subclass of another class, then its power class is a subclass of that other class's power class.  Left-to-right implication of Exercise 18 of [TakeutiZaring] p. 18. ~ sspwimpcf , using conventional notation, was translated from its virtual deduction form, ~ sspwimpcfVD , using a translation program.  (Contributed by Alan Sare, 13-Jun-2015.)  (Proof modification is discouraged.) (New usage is discouraged.)
